    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing about 850 species of woody trees, shrubs, and vines native to tropical and semi-warm temperate zones. Fig species are characterized by their unique inflorescence and distinctive pollination syndrome, utilizing specific wasp species for pollination.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
